name: CryptoMushrooms #001 - Stropharia Aeruginosa
description: This startling slimy mushroom most know as “Verdigris Agaric” is a rare find occurring mainly in lawns, woodlands and roadsides from spring to autumn in Britain, Europe, Asia and and parts of North America, in alkaline and humus-rich areas. Most sources claim that it is highly poisonous, although effects are not well known and its toxic constituents undescribed.
